course_title: Topics in Symbolic Logic - TOPICS:SYMB LOGI

002.comments: Prerequisites: in addition to PHIL 220, students must have completed at least one of PHIL 320, 322, or 323 prior to taking this course, with completion of PHIL 320 being strongly recommended.

description: Formal semantics, proof theory, incompleteness and decidability, axiomatic set theory, independence results. Consult the Department as to which topics are offered in a given year.
